22/02/2006
VIENNA, Austria -- President Heinz Fischer said on Tuesday (21 February) that his country expects Austrian nationals who fled Croatia after WWII to receive their due compensation from Zagreb.
Fischer's comment followed talks in Vienna Tuesday (21 February) with Croatian Parliament Speaker Vladimir Seks.
A bilateral agreement on compensation reached between Vienna and Zagreb last year has been criticised by both President Stipe Mesic and opposition parties in Croatia.
In other news, the trade unions in Croatia's civil service sector plan a three-day strike starting on Friday.
The workers are seeking higher wages.
(HRT - 21/02/06)
